node.text: What an incredible honor to speak to the @VP and Sarah Audelo from @allianceforyouthaction about youth voting and voting rights this morning. As an upcoming first-time voter, I understand the importance of using my voice to uplift my peers and encourage them to vote for the change we want to see. We all have to become more educated. While I hate to call myself an activist, I’m a young human who is civically engaged, and to be able to talk to two incredible women trying to make a change in our world for young people means a lot! We have a lot of work to do, but conversations like this make me hopeful. ♥️

node.text: Y’all, this video has me crying in the club. The crazy thing is the video doesn’t even capture fully how much fun we had. The love I felt. For people to travel far and wide to celebrate ME. That’s REAL LOVE. Here’s a lil look at the best birthday celebration of the year, in my opinion. 🇬🇷✨♥️ (thank you @destiny1of1 fir vid)

node.text: Namaste y'all! Episode 5 of #ChopItUp is now live! I had so much fun Saluting the Sun and getting into a Warriors Pose with my big sis @aokileesimmons! We talked about so much from ethical technology to women empowerment, I hope y'all enjoy this episode of #ChopItUp! And a special thank you to @esmezzer for being a great Yoga teacher! #Namaste 🕉 🧘🏾‍♀️🧘🏾‍♀️

node.text: Today is the day!!! #ChopItUp Episode 1 is here. I loved being in conversation with one of my favorite humans, @sayeedshahidi. Perfect timing to celebrate Valentine’s and his 18th birthday which happen to be the same day ❤️ Big ups to everyone involved. I love y’all dearly. @aseedandwings team, WE DID IT. And I can’t forget @facebookwatch family. Thank you for believing in us, seeing us, and giving us all the creative power to bring our vision to life. It’s only up from here. I hope y’all enjoy it. Xo. Upward and onward. ♥️✨#blacklove #valentines

node.text: I’m so excited for y’all to check out the trailer for my new show “Chop It Up” presented by @facebookwatch and @aseedandwings premiering this Friday, Feb 12th at 10 a.m. Catch me and the homies hanging out while I whip up their favorite dish and get their take on everything from dating to mental health to technology! A big shout out to @sayeedshahidi @choycebrown @nilesfitch @kyladrew @aokileesimmons @marsaimartin for being a part of the show and supporting my filmmaking efforts 🍽🗣✨#ChopItUp

UH OH, IT'S MY SISTERS BIRTHDAY!!! Thanks for all you've taught me. You wear many hats when it comes to me, and you don't have to. Grateful you’re my sister. You're my favorite person to annoy. 🙃 Happy Birthday, shawty. I love you to the moon. ♥️✨ @ps_iiloveyou

node.text: What an incredible honor to speak to the @VP and Sarah Audelo from @allianceforyouthaction about youth voting and voting rights this morning. As an upcoming first-time voter, I understand the importance of using my voice to uplift my peers and encourage them to vote for the change we want to see. We all have to become more educated. While I hate to call myself an activist, I’m a young human who is civically engaged, and to be able to talk to two incredible women trying to make a change in our world for young people means a lot! We have a lot of work to do, but conversations like this make me hopeful. ♥️
